Canadaâ€™s election campaign heads
into its final week with Prime Minister Stephen Harper leading
in the  polls .  WHAT TO WATCH: *Prime Minister Stephen Harper campaigns for the
May 2 federal election at events in Sault Ste. Marie and
Windsor, Ontario. Liberal Leader Michael Ignatieff is in Thunder
Bay, Ontario and Vancouver, while  New Democratic Party  Leader
Jack Layton will be in Saint John, New Brunswick and Gatineau,
Quebec. Support for the New Democratic Party rose to 23 percent
compared with 18 percent in the 2008 election, according to a
CTV/Globe/Nanos poll released April 23.  MARKETS:
*The S&P/TSX Composite Index gained 0.5 percent to 13,972.02 on
Thursday, its third consecutive gain.
*Yields on two-year Government of Canada bonds were unchanged at
1.81 percent in Toronto.
*The Canadian dollar rose to 95.32 cents per  U.S. dollar . One
